<br>
That said If you find yourself in need of some pp around lev 54, I highly recomend Cobalt Scar for the best exp/pp combo around...<br>
<br>
You can sell the gems (be sure and print a list of them all, some you will want for Vellious armour) you don't need, you can sell the pelts, and you can get nice exp all at once...I LOVE that zone  :-) I was averaging 1000pp in gems/loot/pelts every day there ....<br>
<br>
The only downside to CS is that it is a popular place for quad kiters, and the spawns can be too few if you play during peak times...However, I found that the tower is usually a good place  even during peak times...Just make some lev rings...Park your pet on the land, malosi the wyvernns (prb. get hit once) and run out the window to your waiting pet, and have fun :-)<br>
<br>
If the Wyvernns, and Drakes are all gone, chances are the Haunted Seachests are free....make some waterstones, and enjoy! They have a lot of HP's, but I've never had trouble with them, and at lev 53-54 I was able to fight them underwater, and by the time I was FM again, another would pop. Nice timing on them, even if it is a bit slower than fighting Wyvernns/Drakes<br>
<br>
The quad kiters also hate the drakes, and thier annoying AoE, which hits for 500dmg, and the dispelling they do, so they are usually available (I've made several Druid friends by killing Drakes while they take the Wyvernns) ...but if you send your pet, and stay out of AoE range they are not that hard at all...Just takes a bit of practice to get the distance down. I can't tell you how many free ports I've gotten from thankfull quad kiting druids/wizards who fear the Drakes which is a nice bonus :-)<br>
<br>
If you haven't mastered baking, you can use the meat from them to make some yummy (and has stats!) food...down at the Othmir camp there is an oven, and a brew tank! (Hell, I even like the happy little tune they play when you are on the beach!)<br>
<br>
btw, I wouldn't bother with the Sirens unless you have a bit of help, and you are doing the 7 shawls quest, and the Bulthars have waaayyyyy too many HP's for the effort...<br>
