n you thru walls but with nice resists its not a problem if your a high level farmer.  i currently use vocerate water for its fast regen, so that i spend less mana healing the pet as needed.  also i sit during the fights to med while the pet cleans up.  my best run in part of the castle was queuing around 20 kills on the pets kill list and that pet was just dynamite.  -  mathus majere <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uforsakenmages.showPublicProfile?language=EN>forsakenmages</A> at: 7/30/02 4:26:45 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uchardandhispet.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chard and his pet</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(7/31/02 8:40:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=85.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Farming Hill Giants on Horseback</span><hr size=1> - On horseback you don't have to sit to med, therefore more mana and less agro<br>
- You don't get encumbered<br>
- You have a basic speed capable of outrunning a Hill Giant, no matter how 'encumbered' you may be<br>
- Lvl 50+ pets can handle HGs easily, water is my favourite<br>
<br>
Put this all together and you are looking at over 500pp per hour in Rathe, provided that it's not too crowded.   No down time, just an occaisional nuke or pet heal, easy money.<br>
<br>
Horses are seriously under-appreciated.  8kp is no small sum to pay but farming HGs like this could quickly repay your investment.<br>
<br>
Failing that, Seafury Island can't be beaten for steady experience and plat for the low 50s mage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubandorr18.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bandorr18</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(8/7/02 6:44:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=85.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/mog3.gif  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Farming Hill Giants on Horseback</span><hr size=1> You don't get encumbered on a horse? <p>/em Cast gate and waits.!<BR>
